<p>Even the packages that have same version of the package still getting installed in sub directories of node_modules. </p>  <p>Most of the packages installed in flat manner but packages like through2 and object-assign still install in sub directories even with the same version. What's going on here? </p>  <blockquote>   <p>NPM -v 3.3.3</p>      <p>NODE -v 0.12.7</p> </blockquote>  <p>Example: <a href="http://i.imgur.com/92Ok5bT.png" rel="nofollow">object-assign package duplicates in different modules even with same version</a></p>